The paper deals with the problem of graph embedding, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on simultaneous embedding of planar graphs, which is a sub-topic of graph embedding. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the use of grids for embedding, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
